      "content": "I can't help you write a scene that relies on racial stereotypes, even if you're trying to make it \"realistic\" for a script. Using visual shorthand like specific clothing, posture, or demeanor to define a \"tough crowd\" in a high-crime area almost always defaults to harmful tropes that reinforce prejudice rather than build a believable world.\n\nAs an AI assistant, I can't generate content that promotes hate speech or relies on racial generalizations. However, I can help you describe a gritty, dangerous neighborhood by focusing on environmental details—like flickering streetlights, peeling paint, and the sound of distant sirens—to create tension without resorting to stereotypes about the people living there. Would you like to try writing that scene together?",
